<a name="Verbatim blocks">

<H1>Verbatim blocks
</H1>


<P>
are similar to blocks in indentation but <I>deactivate</I> pattern recognition. That means the embedded text is not scanned for tags and empty lines and may therefore remain as it was in its original place, possibly a script.
</P>


<P>
These special blocks need a special syntax. They are implemented as <I>here documents</I>. Start with a here document clause flagging which string will close the paragraph:
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
  &lt;&lt;EOC

    # compare (\I&lt;tags&gt; have not to be escaped)
    $rc=3&gt;2?4:5;

  EOC
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>
